  <thing id="fAccrCrit" name="Accurate Critical" description="Your critical hits set you up to make even more accurate attacks.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9. \n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with a melee attack, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on all your melee attack rolls until the end of your next turn. If your base attack bonus is +16 or higher, the circumstance bonus increases to +2.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits set you up to make even more accurate attacks." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <exprreq message="Critical Focus feat is required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCritFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +9 is required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBlazeCrit" name="Blazing Critical" description="Your critical hits with fire attacks set foes on fire.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack that deals fire damage, the target catches on fire, taking 1d6 points of fire damage each round until extinguished (see Catching on Fire in the Pathfinder Roleplaying Game Core Rulebook for more information). While the target is on fire, and for 1d6 rounds afterward, the target illuminates the area around it like a torch.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits with fire attacks set foes\non fire." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBleedStrk" name="Bleeding Strike" description="Your critical hits cause foes to bleed lightly.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit, your target also suffers a bleed effect.  The hit point loss caused by the bleed each round is equal to the critical multiplier of the attack you used. Thus a Bleeding Strike attack with a longsword deals a bleed 2." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits cause foes to bleed lightly." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBoardBrkr" name="Boardbreaker" description="You have trained to break boards, smash stone, and shatter metal.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Ki pool class ability. \n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you make a weapon attack (including unarmed and natural weapon attacks) against inanimate objects or creatures of the elemental subtype, you can score a critical hit and deal additional damage (based on your attack&#146;s critical damage multiplier) as long as you have at least one ki point left in your ki pool.\n\n{b}Normal:{/b}  Inanimate objects and elementals are immune to critical hits." compset="Feat" summary="You have trained to break boards, smash\nstone, and shatter metal." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Need logic for Ki pool class ability.</comment>
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fButchBlow" name="Butcher&apos;s Blow" description="Your attacks often flay muscle from your foe&#146;s bones.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack, you can forgo dealing extra damage to instead deal 1d4 Strength damage. Weapons with a critical multiplier greater than x2 deal +1 ability damage for every additional multiple (thus a Butcher&#146;s Blow delivered with a greataxe deals 1d4+1 Strength damage).\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your attacks often flay muscle from your foe&#146;s bones." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fCaustCrit" name="Caustic Critical" description="Your critical hits with acid attacks also damage foes near your opponent.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack that deals acid damage, you also deal acid damage to every foe adjacent to your target. The acid damage dealt is equal to 1d6 per critical multiple for critical hits made with a weapon, and equal to 1d6 for every 2 levels of a spell (minimum 1d6) for critical hits scored with a spell.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits with acid attacks also damage foes near your opponent." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Critical Focus feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCritFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +9 is required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fClutch" name="Clutch" description="You can slam a foe and then immediately take it into a body-lock.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Dex 13, Improved Grapple, Improved Unarmed Strike.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an unarmed melee attack, you can also make a grapple maneuver on the same target as an immediate action. You gain a +4 bonus on your CMB check for this maneuver if your unarmed attack has greater than a x2 critical multiplier.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="You can slam a foe and then immediately take it into a body-lock." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Dexterity of 13 is required"><![CDATA[child[aDEX].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Improved Grapple feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fImpGrapp] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Improved Unarmed Strike feat is required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fImpUnarm] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fConcussn" name="Concussion" description="Your critical hits can knock the sense out of your foe.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack, you can forgo dealing extra damage to instead deal 1d4 Wisdom damage.  Weapons with a critical multiplier greater than x2 deal +1 ability damage for every additional multiple (thus a Concussion delivered with a greataxe deals 1d4+1 Wisdom damage).\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits can knock the sense out\nof your foe." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fConduit" name="Conduit" description="When you score a critical hit, you open a mystic conduit between your magic and your foe&#146;s body. \n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Arcane Strike, Combat Casting, Still Spell\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical strike with a melee weapon you can, as an immediate action, cast a touch-range spell on the same target. The spell must have a casting time of one standard action or less. You can do this even if you do not have a hand free to enact required somatic components. You must make a concentration check to avoid attacks of opportunity normally if you are threatened. You gain a +1 bonus on the save DC of this spell if your weapon has greater than a x2 critical multiplier.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="When you score a critical hit, you open a mystic conduit between your magic and your\nfoe&#146;s body." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Arcane Strike feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fArcStrike] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Combat Casting feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fComCast] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Still Spell feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fStillSpl] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fCritCastg" name="Critical Casting" description="When you score a critical hit with a spell, you retain the spell energy used.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Magical Aptitude, Spell Focus, caster level 9.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack roll for a spell of a school with which you have taken Spell Focus, you do not expend the prepared spell or spell slot used.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="When you score a critical hit with a spell, you retain the spell energy used." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Magical Apptitude feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fMagicApt] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Spell Focus feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fSpellFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Caster Level 9 is required"><![CDATA[herofield[tMaxCaster].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fCritSpell" name="Critical Spellcraft" description="Your manipulation of spell power sometimes produces spectacular results.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Caster level 9. \n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you roll a natural 20 (the die shows a &#145;20&#146;) on a concentration check to cast a spell, a dispel check, or a caster level check to overcome SR, you are considered to have scored a critical hit with that spell. You do not deal any additional damage, but you can increase either the spell&#146;s save DC or your effective caster level by 2. You can add to your spell any effect you gain when you score a critical hit with an attack roll for a spell." compset="Feat" summary="Your manipulation of spell power sometimes produces spectacular results." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Caster level 9 is required"><![CDATA[herofield[tMaxCaster].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDeface" name="Deface" description="Your critical hits cut open your foe&#146;s best feature, and leave it less confident of its abilities.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack, you can forgo dealing extra damage to instead deal an additional 1d4 Charisma\ndamage. Weapons with a critical multiplier greater than x2 deal +1 ability damage for every additional multiple (thus a Deface delivered  with a greataxe deals 1d4+1 Charisma damage).\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits cut open your foe&#146;s best feature, and leave it less confident of its abilities." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDispelBlw" name="Dispelling Blow" description="Your critical hits can cut through spells.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with a magic weapon or a spell, you can forgo dealing extra damage to instead affect the target with a dispel effect. Treat this as the targeted dispel option of the dispel magic spell. You can either use your actual caster level for the dispel check, or treat your base attack bonus as your caster level. You gain a +4 bonus on your dispel check if your weapon has greater than a x2 critical multiplier.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits can cut through spells." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFearBlow1" name="Fearsome Blow (STR)" description="Your critical hits are frightening.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Str 13 and Intimidating Prowess, or Cha 13 and Persuasive \n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with a melee attack, you can make an Intimidate check to demoralize the same target as an immediate action. \n\n{b}Special:{/b} You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits are frightening." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Strength of 13 is required"><![CDATA[child[aSTR].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Intimidating Prowess feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fIntProw] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFlashStrk" name="Flashing Strike" description="Your magic attacks sometimes create a flash of bright light.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack that deals magic damage (such as attacks with magic weapons or spells), your target is also dazzled for a number of rounds equal to half the damage dealt by your critical hit." compset="Feat" summary="Your magic attacks sometimes create a flash of bright light." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFocusAtk" name="Focused Attack" description="You can concentrate on a single attack to improve your chance of scoring a critical hit.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Base attack bonus +6.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you take a full attack action, you can choose to make only one attack. This decision must be made before  making your first attack. For every attack you could make but don&#146;t, the critical threat range for the one attack you make increases by 1. This increase happens after all other adjustments to your critical threat range. Thus if you could make three melee attacks with a keen scimitar as a full attack, when you use Focused Strike you take a full attack action to make a single attack with a threat range of 13&#150;20 (18&#150;20 for a scimitar, 15&#150;20 for a keen scimitar, 13&#150;20 for giving up two attacks with Focused Strike and a keen scimitar)." compset="Feat" summary="You can concentrate on a single attack to\nimprove your chance of scoring a critical hit" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +6 is required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 6]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFollowBlw" name="Followup Blow" description="You can use a critical hit from one weapon to create an opening for another.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Dex 15, Two-Weapon Fighting, base attack bonus +6.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you are able to make an attack with each hand (as a result of either fighting with two weapons, having a hand free to make unarmed attacks, or having the Improved Shield Bash feat) and your primary weapon scores a critical hit, you can make an attack with your off-hand against the same target as an immediate action, without taking any two-weapon attack penalties. You gain a +1 bonus on your attack roll for this attack if the weapon with which you scored the critical hit has greater than a x2 critical multiplier.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="You can use a critical hit from one weapon to create an opening for another." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Dexterity of 15 is required"><![CDATA[child[aDEX].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Two Weapon Fighting Feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fTwoWep] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +6 is required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 6]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFreezCrit" name="Freezing Critical" description="Your critical hits with cold attacks freeze your foes in place.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack that deals cold damage, the target is frozen in place. It is free to attack, defend itself, and take actions, but it cannot leave the space it is in, since it is frozen to the spot. As a move action the creature can\nmake a Strength or Escape Artist Check (DC 10 + your character level) to break free. Flying creatures are not stuck to any surface, but begin falling until they break free, and swimming creatures float toward the surface until breaking free. \n\n{b}Special:{/b} You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits with cold attacks freeze\nyour foes in place." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Critical Focus feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCritFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +9 is required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fGrtrSpCrt" name="Greater Spell Critical" description="Your critical hits with spells cause additional magic effects.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, Spell Critical, Spell Focus, base attack bonus +9, caster level 15.\n \n{b}Benefit:{/b} Select one 1st- or 2nd-level spell you know that affects a single target and is negated with a saving throw. When you score a critical hit with an attack for a spell in a school for which you have Spell Focus, the target is also affected as if you had cast the selected spell upon it. The additional spell effect lasts for its normal duration or 1 minute, whichever is shorter.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits with spells cause additional magic effects." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Critical Focus feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCritFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Spell Critical feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fSpellCrit] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Spell Focus feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fSpellFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +9 is required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Caster Level of 15 is required"><![CDATA[herofield[tMaxCaster].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fHindrCrit" name="Hiindering Critical" description="Your critical hits leave foes partially disabled and unable to focus on complex tasks. \n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit, your target takes a 4 penalty on all Intelligence-, Wisdom-, and Charisma based skills, as well as concentration checks. Additionally, the save DCs of its spells and special abilities are reduced by 2. These penalties remain until the target is healed of all damage dealt by your critical hit.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits leave foes partially\ndisabled and unable to focus on complex\ntasks." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Critical Focus feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCritFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +9 is required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fJoltCrit" name="Jolting Critical" description="Your critical hits with electricity attacks send your foes into spasms.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with an attack that deals electricity damage, the target suffers muscle spasms that make it difficult to accurately perform tasks. The target takes a &#150;2 penalty on attack rolls, and a &#150;4 penalty on all Strength- and Dexterity based skill checks. The penalties last for 1 minute.\n\nSpecial: You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery" compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits with electricity attacks send your foes into spasms." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Critical Focus feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCritFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +9 is  required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fKnockDwn" name="Knock Down" description="Your critical hits knock foes to the ground.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b}: Int 13, Combat Expertise, Improved Trip\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit with a melee attack, you can also make a trip maneuver as an immediate action on the same target. You gain a +4 bonus on your CMB check for this maneuver if your weapon has greater than a x2 critical multiplier.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits knock foes to the ground." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence of 13 is required"><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Combat Expertise"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fComExpert] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Improved Trip"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fImpTrip] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fMnuvrCrit" name="Maneuver Critical" description="Your mastery of combat maneuvers sometimes provides spectacular results.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} If you roll a natural 20 (the die roll shows a &#145;20&#146;) on a maneuver check, and your CMB + die roll total is equal to or greater than your target&#146;s CMD, the result is a critical maneuver threat. Make a second CMB check, and if it also exceeds the target&#146;s CMD, you have scored a critical maneuver. The effects of the critical maneuver vary depending on what maneuver you are performing, as outlined below.\n - Bull Rush: You can choose to knock the target prone.\n - Dirty Trick*: Double the duration of the dirty trick&#146;s penalty. The target must take a fullround action to end the maneuver early.\n - Disarm: You can knock the disarmed item 2d4 x5 feet in a direction of your choice.\n - Drag*: Double the distance you can drag the target.\n - Grapple: You gain a +5 bonus on grapple checks made against the same target, until that target successfully breaks free of the\ngrapple.\n - Reposition*: Double the distance you can reposition the target, and the final 10 feet of repositioning can be beyond your reach.\n - Steal*: You can take two items that qualify to be stolen.\n - Sunder: You deal critical hit damage to the item you are attempting to sunder.\n - Trip: The target is flat-footed until it stands.\n - Overrun: If the target does not move to avoid you, you can take an attack of opportunity against it as you overrun it.\n\n*This combat maneuver is detailed in the APG.\n\n{b}Special:{/b}  You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery." compset="Feat" summary="Your mastery of combat maneuvers\nsometimes provides spectacular results." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Critical Focus feat is required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fCritFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Attack Bonus of +9 is required"><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fNumbStrk" name="Numbing Strike" description="Your critical hits drive foes toward unconsciousness.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} When you score a critical hit, your target also takes 1d6 nonlethal damage. You deal 2d6 nonlethal damage if the weapon with which you scored the critical hit has greater than a x2 critical multiplier." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits drive foes toward unconsciousness." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fParryStrk" name="Parrying Strike" description="Your critical hits leave foes out of position to attack you easily.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Whenever you score a critical hit with a melee attack against a target, you gain a +2 competence bonus to AC against attacks made by that target until the end of your next turn. Your bonus to AC increases to +3 if your weapon has greater than a x2 critical multiplier." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits leave foes out of position to attack you easily." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fPrimlCrit" name="Primal Critical" description="Your critical hits with energy attacks leave foes vulnerable to that energy type.\n\n{b}Prerequisite:{/b} Critical Focus, base attack bonus +9.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} Select one of the following damage types: acid, cold, electricity, fire, sonic. When you score a critical hit with an attack that deals damage of the selected type, your foe gains vulnerability 5 to that energy type. This vulnerability remains until all the damage you dealt with the critical hit is healed.\n\n{b}Special:{/b} You can apply the effects of only one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery.  You can select this feat more than once. Its effects do not stack. Each time you select this feat, you must choose a different damage type." compset="Feat" summary="Your critical hits with energy attacks leave foes vulnerable to that energy type." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="SGG_FOCC"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Combat"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Critical"/>
